highlights.description: Libraries can be instrumental in stoking the love of reading at an early age.
Librarians act as guides to unlocking the joys of reading for children who stay in libraries after school.

The first time I thought of libraries as public infrastructure counterpart for neighborhoods without other third spaces like grocery stores. What are some other public goods (like parks) that libraries can complement as a bolstered neighborhood gathering point?
Great that a new library can also be a place of civic engagement, especially if politicians find it an important place to mingle with the community.
